Subject: rPSA-2007-0143-1 mysql mysql-bench mysql-server

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0143-1
Published: 2007-07-17
Products: rPath Linux 1
Rating: Major
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote User Deterministic Denial of Service
Updated Versions:
    mysql=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/5.0.45-0.1-1
    mysql-bench=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/5.0.45-0.1-1
    mysql-server=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/5.0.45-0.1-1

References:
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1536
    http://lists.mysql.com/announce/470

Description:
    Previous versions of the mysql package contain multiple
    vulnerabilities, the most serious of which allows an
    attacker to crash the mysql server (Denial of Service).
    Other vulnerabilities allow users to gain escalated
    privileges within the database server, including update
    privileges.

